      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Identifying Guam",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "centeredImage",
          "imageUrl": "/images/guam/0_gu_summary.png"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_location.png",
              "imageLink": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/75/Guam_in_Oceania_%28-mini_map_-rivers%29.svg/2388px-Guam_in_Oceania_%28-mini_map_-rivers%29.svg.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Guam is a United States overseas territory. As such, it is counted as **the US** for country streaks purposes."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_car.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/VRiC7utYWhZZjnsm9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The entire Google car is blurred, however an **antenna** at the front right and a tiny part of the **roof rack** can be seen.",
              "NOTE: You will not see a roof rack on the Northern Mariana Islands Google car."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_pole.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/jPup4bbtnzrAwtpM7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Poles on Guam are almost always **concrete** and commonly very thick.",
              "NOTE: Northern Mariana Islands typically have wooden poles."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "pole"
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/streetsign.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/FCLP4g95945UNCAs8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Guam uses **green** street signs, unlike the Northern Mariana Islands, which use blue street signs."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_landscape.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/dquWaVahW6qV5rSY8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Guam has a **tropical climate** with a lot of dense and somewhat low vegetation."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_reflectorspam.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/rV74Bk4bBnfL1emp9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Both Guam and Northern Mariana Islands often have a very **large number** of **road reflectors**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_asian.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/5nqPw4zR28Bqm25w5",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "**East Asian languages** such as Japanese, Chinese, Korean, and even Russian are common to see in Guam.",
              "NOTE: This is also the case in Northern Mariana Islands."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Regional clues",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_coverage.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/guam/gu_coverage.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Coverage in Guam is fairly limited, particularly in the southern half, where there is almost no coverage inland."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_hillysouth.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/542NLfJXbMdfNzQE9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "**Hills** are mostly found on the southern half of the island."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_flatnorth.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/FTkRJj1AEnDoWnwP8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Similarly, the northern half of the island is mostly **flat**."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Spotlight",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/Apra_View_Hint.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/AKPVwkAEFB5Wjyes6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Some Signposts near the town of Apra View are coloured **yellow**."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/guam/gu_leopalace.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/mXQvkj25qFMZJRJR8",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "LeoPalace Resort can be recognised by the white, resort buildings with **orange tiled roofs**, which looks superficially similar to tiled roofs found on [Java](https://goo.gl/maps/E6P4UxfQsHz8wZoe7)."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
